SEPTEMBER 15, 1991 | The Association of National Security Alumni is opposed to the use of covert operations. Mr. MacMichael discussed the operations of the CIA and the intelligence community. The weakening of the Central Intelligence Agency vis a vis the Department of Defense is also discussed. MacMichael briefly addresses the INSLAW case and the death of Danny Casolaro which occurred three weeks prior to this taping. He briefly addresses the career of James Jesus Angleton.

